{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770053278,"nonce":"k0vEdW8mfXu9gb34Szqw3PR+TCI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nsMlI","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/131","origin":"github"},"title":"[Agent Rules] Add guidance for ROS 2 package licensing","message":"## Problem\n\nAgents need clear guidance on how to handle licensing when creating or modifying ROS 2 packages. Currently, agents may assume a license (e.g., Apache 2.0, BSD-3-Clause) without checking project-specific licensing requirements.\n\n## Current Behavior\n\nWhen adding copyright headers to files, agents:\n- Make assumptions about license type\n- Don't check for existing LICENSE files in the repository\n- May use inconsistent licenses across files in the same package\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\nAgents should:\n1. **First**: Check for LICENSE file in the repository root\n2. **Second**: Check package.xml for `\u003clicense\u003e` tag\n3. **Third**: Examine existing source files for copyright header patterns\n4. **Only then**: Choose appropriate license header format\n\n## Standard ROS 2 License Patterns\n\nCommon ROS 2 licenses to recognize:\n- **Apache 2.0** - Most common for ROS 2 packages\n- **BSD-3-Clause** - Common for academic projects\n- **MIT** - Common for simpler packages\n\n## Implementation\n\nAdd to `.agent/knowledge/ros2_development_patterns.md`:\n- Section on \"Copyright and Licensing\"\n- Decision tree for determining correct license\n- Template headers for common licenses\n- Examples of checking LICENSE and package.xml\n\nAdd to `.agent/AI_RULES.md`:\n- Rule: \"Always check project licensing before adding headers\"\n- Rule: \"Match existing copyright patterns in the repository\"\n\n## Example Workflow\n\n```bash\n# 1. Check for LICENSE file\ncat LICENSE  # or LICENSE.txt, COPYING, etc.\n\n# 2. Check package.xml\ngrep '\u003clicense\u003e' package.xml\n\n# 3. Check existing source files\nhead -20 src/existing_file.cpp\n\n# 4. Use matching format for new files\n```\n\n## Priority\n\nHigh - Licensing errors can create legal/compliance issues\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}